---
/**
 * rest-api/0005 · Figure 2 — "breaking vs non-breaking changes".
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/rest-api/lessons/0005-api-versioning-strategies.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption incl. the footnote <sup>). Lives as an .astro
 * component, NOT inline in the MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with
 * raw inline SVG that uses kebab-case attributes. This figure uses no arrowhead
 * markers, so it needs no <defs>.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 232"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Non-breaking changes are pure additions shipped in place; breaking changes remove, rename, retype, or tighten and force a new version"
    >
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="320"
                y="18"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">BREAKING vs NON-BREAKING</text
            >
            <!-- safe column -->
            <rect
                x="8"
                y="30"
                width="300"
                height="184"
                rx="10"
                fill="#eef5ee"
                stroke="#2f5d3a"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text
                x="158"
                y="50"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">✓ NON-BREAKING · ship in place</text
            >
            <text x="158" y="66" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#244a2e"
                >pure additions · no version · no migration</text
            >
            <rect x="24" y="76" width="268" height="26" rx="6" fill="#fff" stroke="#2f5d3a"></rect>
            <text x="34" y="93" font-size="10" fill="#244a2e">+ add an optional request field</text>
            <rect x="24" y="106" width="268" height="26" rx="6" fill="#fff" stroke="#2f5d3a"></rect>
            <text x="34" y="123" font-size="10" fill="#244a2e">+ add a response field</text>
            <rect x="24" y="136" width="268" height="26" rx="6" fill="#fff" stroke="#2f5d3a"></rect>
            <text x="34" y="153" font-size="10" fill="#244a2e">+ add a new endpoint</text>
            <rect x="24" y="166" width="268" height="36" rx="6" fill="#fff" stroke="#2f5d3a"></rect>
            <text x="34" y="182" font-size="10" fill="#244a2e">+ add an optional enum value —</text>
            <text x="34" y="195" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                ><tspan font-style="italic">only</tspan> if clients tolerate unknowns</text
            >
            <!-- breaking column -->
            <rect
                x="332"
                y="30"
                width="300"
                height="184"
                rx="10"
                fill="#f7ecea"
                stroke="#9a2417"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text
                x="482"
                y="50"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">✗ BREAKING · forces a version</text
            >
            <text x="482" y="66" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#7a2218"
                >can break a deployed client silently</text
            >
            <rect x="348" y="76" width="268" height="26" rx="6" fill="#fff" stroke="#9a2417"></rect>
            <text x="358" y="93" font-size="10" fill="#7a2218">− remove or rename a field</text>
            <rect x="348" y="106" width="268" height="26" rx="6" fill="#fff" stroke="#9a2417"
            ></rect>
            <text x="358" y="123" font-size="10" fill="#7a2218"
                >↻ change a field's type or meaning</text
            >
            <rect x="348" y="136" width="268" height="26" rx="6" fill="#fff" stroke="#9a2417"
            ></rect>
            <text x="358" y="153" font-size="10" fill="#7a2218"
                >! make an optional field required</text
            >
            <rect x="348" y="166" width="268" height="36" rx="6" fill="#fff" stroke="#9a2417"
            ></rect>
            <text x="358" y="182" font-size="10" fill="#7a2218"
                >⊘ tighten validation · change a</text
            >
            <text x="358" y="195" font-size="10" fill="#7a2218"
                >&#160;&#160;&#160;default · drop an endpoint/enum</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        The catch on enum values: adding one is safe <em>only if</em> clients already ignore values they
        don't recognize. Server only adds; client only tolerates.<sup
            ><a href="#s3" id="r3">3</a></sup
        >
    </figcaption>
</figure>
